description: This Python source file defines data models related to execution workflows, including specifications for environments, execution requests, summaries, details, logs, and responses, primarily using Pydantic models. It also includes enum definitions for environment and status states.

classes.name: ExecutionEnvironment
classes.description: Enumeration of possible execution environments, such as local, airflow, or simulated.

classes.name: ExecutionStatus
classes.description: Enumeration of possible statuses for an execution, such as queued, running, completed, failed, etc.

classes.name: GitSource
classes.description: Model representing the Git repository details, including URL, branch, commit, and subpath.

classes.name: ExecutionRequest
classes.description: Model for submitting an execution request, including git source, entrypoint, parameters, environment, and optional metadata.

classes.name: ExecutionSummary
classes.description: Model for minimal execution metadata used in listings and overviews.

classes.name: ExecutionDetail
classes.description: Extended model containing full details about an execution, including result, error, and logs pointer.

classes.name: LogsResponse
classes.description: Model representing the logs associated with an execution, including lines and pagination info.

classes.name: SubmitResponse
classes.description: Model for the response after submitting an execution request, including execution ID and initial status.

classes.name: MonitoringInfo
classes.description: Model providing self-monitoring information about the service, including uptime and execution counts.
